web: gunicorn app:app


# Gunicorn (Green Unicorn) is a Python WSGI HTTP server that is commonly used to serve Python web applications, especially for  frameworks like Django, Flask, and FastAPI. It acts as an interface between your web application and the web server, handling incoming HTTP requests and routing them to your application. #

# WSGI-compliant: Gunicorn is a WSGI (Web Server Gateway Interface) server, which is the standard interface between Python web applications and web servers. #